00:53:24,266 --> 00:53:25,426
CEDRlC: Grab him!

799
00:53:30,139 --> 00:53:31,504
[Elevator bell rings]

800
00:53:41,083 --> 00:53:43,517
CONClERGE: You little sh--

801
00:53:45,087 --> 00:53:47,385
I've committed credit card fraud.

802
00:53:47,423 --> 00:53:49,687
CONClERGE: Get me security!

803
00:53:49,725 --> 00:53:53,058
We've got to stop that delinquent!

804
00:53:53,095 --> 00:53:55,359
Come along, Cedric.

805
00:54:13,983 --> 00:54:15,951
I've had enough of this vacation.

806
00:54:15,985 --> 00:54:17,612
I'm going home.

807
00:54:28,130 --> 00:54:29,859
Hold it right there.

808
00:54:32,101 --> 00:54:33,762
This is the concierge, sir!

809
00:54:34,637 --> 00:54:36,867
I knew it was you.

810
00:54:36,905 --> 00:54:39,100
I could smell you getting off the elevator.

811
00:54:41,310 --> 00:54:44,006
You was here last night, too, wasn't you?

812
00:54:46,048 --> 00:54:49,449
Yes, sir...I was.

813
00:54:49,485 --> 00:54:50,952
JOHNNY: You was here...

814
00:54:51,020 --> 00:54:53,352
and you was smooching with my brother!

815
00:54:55,658 --> 00:54:58,752
I'm--I'm afraid you're mistaken, sir.

816
00:54:58,794 --> 00:55:00,284
Don't give me that.

817
00:55:00,329 --> 00:55:02,320
You been smooching with everybody!

818
00:55:02,364 --> 00:55:05,231
Snuffy, Al, Leo...

819
00:55:05,267 --> 00:55:07,030
Iittle Mo with the gimpy leg...

820
00:55:07,069 --> 00:55:09,469
Cheeks, Bony Bob, Cliff.

821
00:55:09,505 --> 00:55:11,029
[Gasps]

822
00:55:13,242 --> 00:55:14,402
No!

823
00:55:16,011 --> 00:55:17,603
It's a lie!

824
00:55:17,680 --> 00:55:19,614
JOHNNY: I could go on forever, baby.

825
00:55:20,582 --> 00:55:22,447
I'm terribly sorry, sir...

826
00:55:22,484 --> 00:55:25,078
but I'm afraid you're mistaken.

827
00:55:25,120 --> 00:55:27,111
We're looking for a young man.

828
00:55:27,156 --> 00:55:28,646
All right.

829
00:55:28,691 --> 00:55:30,352
I believe you...

830
00:55:30,392 --> 00:55:31,825
but my Tommy gun don't!

831
00:55:33,195 --> 00:55:36,028
Get down on your knees and tell me you love me.

832
00:55:38,701 --> 00:55:40,259
CONClERGE: On your knees.

833
00:55:49,311 --> 00:55:52,007
I love you!

834
00:55:55,351 --> 00:55:57,216
You got to do betterthan that!

835
00:55:58,721 --> 00:56:00,951
EVERYONE: I love you!

836
00:56:02,691 --> 00:56:05,888
JOHNNY: Maybe I'm off my hinges, but I believe you.

837
00:56:05,928 --> 00:56:08,021
That's why I'm going to let you go.

838
00:56:09,098 --> 00:56:11,760
I'm going to give you to the count of three...

839
00:56:11,800 --> 00:56:15,930
to get your lousy, lying, lowdown...

840
00:56:15,971 --> 00:56:18,599
four-flushing carcass out my door!

841
00:56:20,476 --> 00:56:21,875
-One. -Open up the door!

842
00:56:21,910 --> 00:56:23,070
Two.

843
00:56:25,514 --> 00:56:27,675
Ha ha ha ha ha!

844
00:56:27,750 --> 00:56:29,217
Ha ha ha ha ha!

845
00:56:29,251 --> 00:56:30,650
[Tommy gun firing]

846
00:56:37,359 --> 00:56:39,088
Three!

847
00:56:39,128 --> 00:56:41,858
JOHNNY: Merry Christmas, you filthy animal...

848
00:56:42,898 --> 00:56:44,695
[Tommy gun fires]

849
00:56:44,733 --> 00:56:46,826
JOHNNY: and a happy New Year.

850
00:56:46,869 --> 00:56:48,166
[Gunshot]

851
00:56:49,505 --> 00:56:50,631
Stay in your rooms!

852
00:56:50,672 --> 00:56:52,469
This is an emergency!

853
00:56:52,508 --> 00:56:55,841
There's an insane guest with a gun!

854
00:57:06,622 --> 00:57:11,286
KEVlN: Nooo!

855
00:57:11,326 --> 00:57:12,486
HARRY: Come to papa!

856
00:57:15,130 --> 00:57:17,121
MARV: Ha! Round trip to Miami.

857
00:57:17,166 --> 00:57:19,361
What's the matter? Get on the wrong plane, squirt?

858
00:57:19,401 --> 00:57:21,369
HARRY: Looks like you won't be needing this, kid.

859
00:57:21,403 --> 00:57:24,133
MARV: American don't fly to the promised land, little buddy.

860
00:57:24,173 --> 00:57:25,834
HARRY: Come on!

861
00:57:27,443 --> 00:57:28,876
HARRY: We spent nine months in jail...

862
00:57:28,911 --> 00:57:31,345
thinking we had the worst luck in the universe.

863
00:57:31,380 --> 00:57:33,348
We were wrong, little buddy.

864
00:57:33,382 --> 00:57:35,850
MARV: We busted out of the clink, and we're doing fine.

865
00:57:35,918 --> 00:57:37,385
We'll be doing even better...

866
00:57:37,419 --> 00:57:39,387
because we're not robbing houses anymore.

867
00:57:39,421 --> 00:57:40,786
Now we're robbing toy stores.

868
00:57:40,823 --> 00:57:42,256
At midnight tonight...

869
00:57:42,291 --> 00:57:43,849
we're hitting Duncan's Toy Chest.

870
00:57:43,926 --> 00:57:46,190
Five floors of cash.

871
00:57:46,228 --> 00:57:48,128
After that, we grab a couple of phony passports--

872
00:57:48,163 --> 00:57:51,223
HARRY: Marv! Marv, you want to shut up?

873
00:57:51,266 --> 00:57:52,392
MARV: What's the difference?

874
00:57:52,434 --> 00:57:54,061
He's not going to talk to anybody...

875
00:57:54,102 --> 00:57:55,899
except maybe a fish.

876
00:57:55,938 --> 00:57:57,371
Or the undertaker.

877
00:57:57,406 --> 00:57:59,374
HARRY: Let's just get him to the subway tunnel.

878
00:57:59,408 --> 00:58:02,070
I'll feel a lot better once we get him on ice.

879
00:58:04,246 --> 00:58:06,043
HARRY: I've got a gun in my pocket.

880
00:58:06,081 --> 00:58:07,207
You open your mouth...

881
00:58:07,249 --> 00:58:09,342
and you'll be spitting gum out through your forehead.

882
00:58:30,405 --> 00:58:31,633
Well, hello.

883
00:58:35,110 --> 00:58:37,704
-He did it. -Did what?

884
00:58:40,449 --> 00:58:41,609
Thanks.

885
00:58:45,587 --> 00:58:46,679
HARRY: Get him, will ya!

886
00:58:46,755 --> 00:58:47,847
MARV: He went in the park.

887
00:58:47,923 --> 00:58:49,049
HARRY: What are you doing?

888
00:58:49,124 --> 00:58:50,284
Get up!

889
00:59:24,960 --> 00:59:26,188
MARV: Overthere!

890
00:59:31,099 --> 00:59:32,225
BOY: Quit it!

891
00:59:32,267 --> 00:59:33,825
-Hey! -Creep!

892
00:59:33,869 --> 00:59:36,064
-Give it! -What are you doing?

893
00:59:36,738 --> 00:59:38,706
MARV: Hey, Harry, I got him.

894
00:59:38,740 --> 00:59:40,264
HARRY: Let me see. That ain't him.

895
00:59:40,309 --> 00:59:42,709
Put him down. That ain't him.

896
00:59:43,378 --> 00:59:45,039
We should've shot him when we had the chance.

897
00:59:45,080 --> 00:59:47,776
I hate pulling a job knowing that creep is on the loose.

898
00:59:47,816 --> 00:59:50,512
MARV: What can he do? Kids are helpless.

899
00:59:50,586 --> 00:59:51,746
HARRY: Not this kid.

900
00:59:51,820 --> 00:59:53,651
MARV: This time, he doesn't have a houseful...

901
00:59:53,689 --> 00:59:56,055
of dangerous goodies to get us with.

902
00:59:56,091 --> 00:59:58,059
He's in the park. He's alone.

903
00:59:58,093 --> 01:00:00,391
Kids are a-scared of the park.

904
01:00:00,429 --> 01:00:02,397
HARRY: Yeah. Grown men come in the park...

905
01:00:02,431 --> 01:00:03,557
and don't leave alive.

906
01:00:03,599 --> 01:00:05,396
MARV: Yeah.

907
01:00:05,434 --> 01:00:07,095
HARRY: Good luck, little fella.

908
01:00:17,913 --> 01:00:19,346
KEVlN: I want to go home.

909
01:00:20,749 --> 01:00:22,216
Mom, where are you?

910
01:00:26,622 --> 01:00:28,886
[Speaking Spanish]

911
01:00:50,612 --> 01:00:52,375
[Telephone rings]

912
01:00:52,414 --> 01:00:53,881
Turn that down.

913
01:00:55,951 --> 01:00:57,384
-Hello. -Kate McCallister, please.

914
01:00:57,419 --> 01:00:59,614
-This is she. -Ma'am, we found your son.

915
01:00:59,688 --> 01:01:02,384
-What? -The police know where Kevin is.

916
01:01:02,424 --> 01:01:03,891
MAN: He's in New York City.

917
01:01:03,925 --> 01:01:05,187
He's in New York.

918
01:01:05,227 --> 01:01:06,785
-New York? -New York?

919
01:01:06,828 --> 01:01:09,388
MAN: He checked into the Plaza with your husband's credit card.

920
01:01:09,431 --> 01:01:13,128
I'm sure he was scared. He's not a troublemaker.

921
01:01:13,168 --> 01:01:15,568
Would you hold just a second?

922
01:01:15,604 --> 01:01:17,504
He used your credit card to check into the Plaza Hotel.

923
01:01:17,539 --> 01:01:19,200
Do they still have him?

924
01:01:19,241 --> 01:01:20,401
Do they have him?

925
01:01:20,442 --> 01:01:22,103
MAN: No, police are still looking.

926
01:01:22,144 --> 01:01:24,044
Damn it!

927
01:01:24,079 --> 01:01:26,604
We're on the next flight out. Thank you.

928
01:01:26,648 --> 01:01:27,876
We're going to New York.

929
01:01:27,916 --> 01:01:29,315
-Yes! -Yes!

930
01:01:30,452 --> 01:01:32,977
He ran away when they questioned him about the card.

931
01:01:33,055 --> 01:01:34,522
He must be so scared.

932
01:01:34,589 --> 01:01:36,819
Would he go to my brother's place?

933
01:01:36,858 --> 01:01:37,984
Aren't they in Paris?

934
01:01:38,026 --> 01:01:39,516
Maybe there's a housesitter.

935
01:01:39,594 --> 01:01:41,391
I thought you said they're renovating.

936
01:02:14,796 --> 01:02:17,230
[Knock on door]

937
01:02:21,503 --> 01:02:23,698
Hello!

938
01:02:23,739 --> 01:02:25,730
Uncle Rob?

939
01:02:25,774 --> 01:02:26,832
Aunt Georgette?

940
01:02:26,875 --> 01:02:29,207
Anybody home?

941
01:02:29,244 --> 01:02:31,075
Hello!

942
01:02:31,113 --> 01:02:32,808
Anybody home?

943
01:02:32,848 --> 01:02:36,249
It's me, your favorite nephew Kevin.

944
01:02:36,318 --> 01:02:38,309
Uncle Rob!

945
01:02:38,386 --> 01:02:40,411
Aunt Georgette!

946
01:03:01,409 --> 01:03:03,400
[Muttering]

947
01:03:23,698 --> 01:03:25,393
Watch it, kid!

948
01:03:25,433 --> 01:03:28,425
Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!

949
01:03:28,470 --> 01:03:31,462
Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!

950
01:03:31,506 --> 01:03:33,497
WOMAN: Hey, looking for somebody...

951
01:03:33,542 --> 01:03:35,737
to read you a bedtime story?

952
01:03:35,777 --> 01:03:38,473
[Laughing]

953
01:03:41,750 --> 01:03:43,183
Taxi!

954
01:03:55,897 --> 01:03:58,331
Boy, it's scary out there.

955
01:04:00,001 --> 01:04:01,400
Ain't much better in here, kid.

956
01:04:28,864 --> 01:04:31,526
I don't want to ever take a vacation like this again.

957
01:05:02,664 --> 01:05:04,222
Where did all you come from?

958
01:05:04,266 --> 01:05:06,234
I may not have enough for everybody.

959
01:05:06,268 --> 01:05:08,259
How hungry are you guys?

960
01:05:09,804 --> 01:05:11,999
Well, you guys ate all my food.

961
01:05:27,389 --> 01:05:30,222
Aah!

962
01:05:35,363 --> 01:05:37,228
Aah!

963
01:05:37,265 --> 01:05:38,425
Aah!

964
01:05:39,367 --> 01:05:41,528
Aah!

965
01:06:11,700 --> 01:06:14,362
Look, I'm sorry I screamed in yourface.

966
01:06:14,402 --> 01:06:16,734
You were just trying to help me, right?

967
01:06:20,308 --> 01:06:21,570
I'm Kevin McCallister.

968
01:06:22,744 --> 01:06:24,507
Your birds are real nice.

969
01:06:25,513 --> 01:06:26,912
I've seen you before.

970
01:06:26,948 --> 01:06:29,473
You had pigeons all over you.

971
01:06:29,551 --> 01:06:31,781
At first, you looked kind of scary.

972
01:06:31,853 --> 01:06:34,321
But when I think about it, it's not so bad.

973
01:06:34,356 --> 01:06:36,449
They must be all over you 'cause they like you.

974
01:06:38,693 --> 01:06:40,820
If I'm bothering you, I can leave.

975
01:06:40,862 --> 01:06:42,727
Am I bothering you?

976
01:06:43,865 --> 01:06:45,127
No.

977
01:06:46,167 --> 01:06:48,761
Good. I'm not a pain in the butt?

978
01:06:50,872 --> 01:06:52,032
No.

979
01:06:56,778 --> 01:06:58,336
Will those pigeons come back on their own...

980
01:06:58,380 --> 01:06:59,779
or do you have to call them?

981
01:07:11,159 --> 01:07:12,319
WOMAN: Give me your hand.

982
01:07:16,398 --> 01:07:17,888
They can hear it.

983
01:07:35,450 --> 01:07:36,974
This is great.

984
01:07:41,289 --> 01:07:42,688
It's pretty cold out.

985
01:07:42,724 --> 01:07:45,192
I could sure go for a cup of hot chocolate.

986
01:07:45,260 --> 01:07:47,694
How about you? My treat.

987
01:07:52,667 --> 01:07:55,397
KEVlN: I'd hate to spend Christmas Eve in Central Park.

988
01:07:55,437 --> 01:07:57,803
Can we go someplace warm?

989
01:07:57,839 --> 01:07:59,932
WOMAN: Yes. I know a place.

990
01:08:07,048 --> 01:08:11,041
[Playing "Adeste Fideles"]

991
01:08:47,422 --> 01:08:48,582
KEVlN: Nice music.

992
01:08:50,258 --> 01:08:52,192
This place is great.

993
01:08:53,261 --> 01:08:55,752
WOMAN: I've heard the world's great music from here.

994
01:08:57,765 --> 01:09:00,256
Ella Fitzgerald, Count Basie...

995
01:09:00,335 --> 01:09:02,326
Frank Sinatra...

996
01:09:02,403 --> 01:09:03,802
Luciano Pavarotti.

997
01:09:09,677 --> 01:09:11,474
So, do you bring your friends up here?

998
01:09:13,314 --> 01:09:15,179
I haven't got many friends.

999
01:09:15,216 --> 01:09:17,616
Oh. Sorry.

1000
01:09:18,253 --> 01:09:19,948
I'm like the birds I care for.

1001
01:09:21,422 --> 01:09:22,753
People pass me in the street.

1002
01:09:22,790 --> 01:09:25,258
They see me, but they try to ignore me.

1003
01:09:25,293 --> 01:09:27,818
They'd prefer I wasn't part of their city.

1004
01:09:27,862 --> 01:09:29,193
Yeah.

1005
01:09:29,230 --> 01:09:31,221
It's sorta like that with my family.

1006
01:09:31,266 --> 01:09:33,234
I'm kinda the pigeon of the house...

1007
01:09:33,268 --> 01:09:35,133
just because I'm the youngest.

1008
01:09:35,970 --> 01:09:37,494
Everyone fights for position.

1009
01:09:38,439 --> 01:09:40,168
Everybody wants to be seen...

1010
01:09:40,208 --> 01:09:41,334
and heard.

1011
01:09:41,376 --> 01:09:43,139
I guess so.

1012
01:09:43,178 --> 01:09:45,237
I'm seen and heard pretty much...

1013
01:09:45,280 --> 01:09:47,271
but then I get sent to my room a lot, too.

1014
01:09:50,285 --> 01:09:52,913
I wasn't always like this, you know.

1015
01:09:52,954 --> 01:09:54,683
Oh. What were you like before?

1016
01:09:56,057 --> 01:09:57,490
I had a job...

1017
01:09:57,525 --> 01:09:59,152
I had a home...

1018
01:09:59,194 --> 01:10:00,320
I had a family.

1019
01:10:00,361 --> 01:10:01,521
Did you have any kids?

1020
01:10:02,764 --> 01:10:03,924
No.

1021
01:10:05,133 --> 01:10:06,259
Oh, I wanted them...

1022
01:10:07,302 --> 01:10:09,270
but the man I loved...

1023
01:10:09,304 --> 01:10:10,771
fell out of love with me.

1024
01:10:11,639 --> 01:10:13,106
That broke my heart.

1025
01:10:14,008 --> 01:10:16,568
And whenever the chance to be loved came along again...

1026
01:10:17,712 --> 01:10:19,043
I ran away from it.

1027
01:10:20,248 --> 01:10:21,943
I stopped trusting people.

1028
01:10:21,983 --> 01:10:23,450
No offense...

1029
01:10:23,484 --> 01:10:26,317
but that seems like sort of a dumb thing to do.

1030
01:10:26,354 --> 01:10:28,879
I was afraid of getting my heart broken again.

1031
01:10:30,024 --> 01:10:32,185
You see, sometimes you can trust a person...

1032
01:10:32,227 --> 01:10:34,695
and then, when things are down...

1033
01:10:34,729 --> 01:10:36,560
they forget about you.

1034
01:10:37,599 --> 01:10:39,328
Maybe they're just too busy.

1035
01:10:39,400 --> 01:10:40,697
Maybe they don't forget about you...

1036
01:10:40,768 --> 01:10:43,396
but they forget to remember you.

1037
01:10:43,471 --> 01:10:45,234
I don't think people mean to forget.

1038
01:10:45,273 --> 01:10:47,503
I think it just happens.

1039
01:10:47,542 --> 01:10:50,204
My grandfather says if my head wasn't screwed on...

1040
01:10:50,245 --> 01:10:51,872
I'd leave it on the school bus.

1041
01:10:51,913 --> 01:10:53,904
I'm just afraid if I do trust someone...

1042
01:10:53,948 --> 01:10:56,246
I'll get my heart broken again.

1043
01:10:56,284 --> 01:10:57,649
KEVlN: I understand that.

1044
01:10:57,685 --> 01:11:00,620
I used to have a really nice pair of roller blades.

1045
01:11:00,655 --> 01:11:03,215
I was afraid I'd wreck them...

1046
01:11:03,258 --> 01:11:04,782
so I kept them in the box.

1047
01:11:04,826 --> 01:11:06,919
-You know what happened? -No.

1048
01:11:06,961 --> 01:11:08,087
I outgrew them.

1049
01:11:08,129 --> 01:11:09,721
I never wore them once outside...

1050
01:11:09,764 --> 01:11:11,959
just in my room a couple of times.

1051
01:11:13,501 --> 01:11:14,968
A person's heart and a person's feelings...

1052
01:11:15,003 --> 01:11:17,096
are very different than skates.

1053
01:11:18,006 --> 01:11:19,268
Well, they're kind of the same thing.

1054
01:11:19,307 --> 01:11:21,275
If you aren't going to use your heart...

1055
01:11:21,309 --> 01:11:23,300
then what's the difference if it gets broken?

1056
01:11:23,344 --> 01:11:25,278
If you just keep it to yourself...

1057
01:11:25,313 --> 01:11:27,543
maybe it'll be like my roller blades--

1058
01:11:27,582 --> 01:11:29,550
when you do decide to try it...

1059
01:11:29,584 --> 01:11:31,211
it won't be any good.

1060
01:11:31,252 --> 01:11:32,719
You should take a chance.

1061
01:11:32,754 --> 01:11:34,278
You got nothing to lose.

1062
01:11:35,790 --> 01:11:37,621
A bit of truth in there somewhere.

1063
01:11:37,659 --> 01:11:39,126
I think so.

