three.

1335
01:37:01,548 --> 01:37:02,879
HARRY: No.

1336
01:37:02,916 --> 01:37:04,577
[Clang]

1337
01:37:04,617 --> 01:37:06,608
MARV: That's four.

1338
01:37:11,324 --> 01:37:12,655
MARV: Come on, Harry.

1339
01:37:12,692 --> 01:37:14,489
HARRY: Marv, are you sure this is safe?

1340
01:37:14,527 --> 01:37:15,960
MARV: Oh, yeah.

1341
01:37:15,995 --> 01:37:18,293
Yup. I worked all the kinks out.

1342
01:37:18,331 --> 01:37:20,196
Solid as a rock.

1343
01:37:34,113 --> 01:37:35,580
[Furniture collapsing]

1344
01:37:37,050 --> 01:37:38,950
HARRY: Like a rock, huh, Marv?

1345
01:37:38,985 --> 01:37:40,612
KEVlN: Hey, do you guys give up?

1346
01:37:40,653 --> 01:37:42,120
Have you had enough pain?

1347
01:37:42,155 --> 01:37:43,315
MARV: Never!

1348
01:37:55,535 --> 01:37:58,026
HARRY: You better say every prayer you ever heard before!

1349
01:37:58,071 --> 01:38:01,063
MARV: I hope your parents got you a tombstone for Christmas!

1350
01:38:03,509 --> 01:38:04,635
Where'd he go?

1351
01:38:05,411 --> 01:38:08,141
I'm up here, and I'm really scared.

1352
01:38:17,757 --> 01:38:18,917
HARRY: What's that sound?

1353
01:38:29,202 --> 01:38:30,829
-Aah! -Aah!

1354
01:38:39,746 --> 01:38:42,044
MARV: That was the sound of a tool chest...

1355
01:38:42,081 --> 01:38:44,641
falling down the stairs.

1356
01:38:44,684 --> 01:38:45,981
HARRY: Oh.

1357
01:38:48,121 --> 01:38:49,247
[Crunch]

1358
01:38:51,090 --> 01:38:52,250
Yes!

1359
01:39:27,160 --> 01:39:28,320
MARV: Over there!

1360
01:39:29,228 --> 01:39:31,423
HARRY: I don't care if I get the chair. I'm killing that kid!

1361
01:39:34,600 --> 01:39:36,659
HARRY: Surrender, kid!

1362
01:39:36,703 --> 01:39:37,829
MARV: He vanished.

1363
01:39:37,870 --> 01:39:39,804
KEVlN: I'm down here, you big horse's ass!

1364
01:39:43,643 --> 01:39:44,735
MARV: Whoa!

1365
01:39:44,811 --> 01:39:46,540
Nice night for a neck injury!

1366
01:39:48,081 --> 01:39:50,879
Suck brick, kid!

1367
01:39:56,189 --> 01:39:57,679
HARRY: Come on, Marv.

1368
01:39:57,724 --> 01:39:59,692
MARV: Oh, I don't know.

1369
01:39:59,726 --> 01:40:01,489
HARRY: I said, come on.

1370
01:40:03,162 --> 01:40:05,824
Come on, you big sissy.

1371
01:40:05,865 --> 01:40:07,856
[Whimpering]

1372
01:40:16,442 --> 01:40:18,410
[Sniffing]

1373
01:40:19,579 --> 01:40:20,978
Harry?

1374
01:40:21,014 --> 01:40:22,481
You wearing aftershave?

1375
01:40:22,515 --> 01:40:24,506
HARRY: That's not aftershave. That's kerosene.

1376
01:40:25,318 --> 01:40:26,842
The rope is soaked in it.

1377
01:40:27,954 --> 01:40:30,252
Why would anybody soak a rope in kerosene?

1378
01:40:34,894 --> 01:40:36,225
Merry Christmas.

1379
01:40:37,430 --> 01:40:39,830
-Go up! -Aah!

1380
01:40:48,775 --> 01:40:49,901
Aah!

1381
01:40:53,646 --> 01:40:55,204
HARRY: Ooch! Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

1382
01:40:55,281 --> 01:40:57,306
Ouch! Aah! Ouch!

1383
01:41:00,787 --> 01:41:02,482
MARV: Aah!

1384
01:41:05,558 --> 01:41:13,021
-Aah! -Aah!

1385
01:41:13,066 --> 01:41:14,363
HARRY: Get off!

1386
01:41:15,768 --> 01:41:17,827
-Aah! -Aah!

1387
01:41:38,858 --> 01:41:40,018
HARRY: Get the bag.

1388
01:41:40,893 --> 01:41:43,487
Hello. The two guys who robbed Duncan's Toy Chest...

1389
01:41:43,529 --> 01:41:46,430
are at Central Park West and 95th Street.

1390
01:41:46,466 --> 01:41:47,592
Look for fireworks.

1391
01:41:47,633 --> 01:41:48,964
Hurry. They got a gun.

1392
01:41:55,708 --> 01:41:56,800
KEVlN: Hey, I'm down here.

1393
01:41:56,876 --> 01:41:59,436
Better come and get me before I call the cops.

1394
01:42:03,549 --> 01:42:05,039
[Bus horn honks]

1395
01:42:07,353 --> 01:42:08,684
Whoa!

1396
01:42:14,794 --> 01:42:17,922
MARV: My, how the tables have turned.

1397
01:42:17,964 --> 01:42:19,659
HARRY: How do you like the ice, kid?

1398
01:42:20,700 --> 01:42:21,962
[Both laughing]

1399
01:42:25,538 --> 01:42:27,699
HARRY: Let's go for a little stroll in the park.

1400
01:42:45,291 --> 01:42:46,553
HARRY: Give me that bag!

1401
01:42:46,592 --> 01:42:47,718
Gimme it.

1402
01:42:52,965 --> 01:42:55,297
These will look great in the photo album.

1403
01:42:56,269 --> 01:42:58,100
You may have won the battle, little dude...

1404
01:42:58,137 --> 01:42:59,968
but you lost the war.

1405
01:43:00,706 --> 01:43:02,765
HARRY: You ought not have messed with us, pal.

1406
01:43:02,842 --> 01:43:04,241
We're dangerous.

1407
01:43:10,283 --> 01:43:12,410
-Harry. -Shut up.

1408
01:43:16,789 --> 01:43:17,915
Harry...

1409
01:43:17,957 --> 01:43:19,788
HARRY: Shut up. I want to enjoy this.

1410
01:43:20,793 --> 01:43:22,522
MARV: Something's wrong.

1411
01:43:23,429 --> 01:43:24,760
Let's get out of here.

1412
01:43:24,797 --> 01:43:25,957
Shut up, I said!

1413
01:43:28,100 --> 01:43:30,227
HARRY: I never made it to the sixth grade, kid...

1414
01:43:30,269 --> 01:43:33,067
and it doesn't look like you're going to, either.

1415
01:43:34,273 --> 01:43:35,740
WOMAN: Let him go!

1416
01:43:36,776 --> 01:43:38,334
Kevin, run!

1417
01:43:40,279 --> 01:43:42,509
Shoot her! Shoot her!

1418
01:43:43,115 --> 01:43:44,241
Shoot her!

1419
01:43:44,283 --> 01:43:45,750
I'm trying to shoot her!

1420
01:43:56,128 --> 01:44:00,155
-Aah! -Aah!

1421
01:44:11,844 --> 01:44:13,573
[Harry muttering]

1422
01:44:16,515 --> 01:44:23,751
Aah!

1423
01:44:25,758 --> 01:44:26,986
Bye! Thanks!

1424
01:44:47,280 --> 01:44:49,248
[Siren]

1425
01:44:53,386 --> 01:44:55,718
OFFlCER: Jeez, it looks like the Fourth of July!

1426
01:44:56,956 --> 01:44:59,015
We'll take the bridge. You guys get the tunnel.

1427
01:44:59,058 --> 01:45:00,548
Let's go. Come on!

1428
01:45:03,195 --> 01:45:04,685
[Harry and Marv muttering]

1429
01:45:08,301 --> 01:45:09,996
Oh, my God!

1430
01:45:10,036 --> 01:45:11,367
[Gunshot]

1431
01:45:20,646 --> 01:45:22,045
OFFlCER: All right, you guys, let's go.

1432
01:45:22,081 --> 01:45:24,015
SECOND OFFlCER: Come on. On yourfeet.

1433
01:45:24,050 --> 01:45:25,210
HARRY: Take it easy.

1434
01:45:29,021 --> 01:45:31,251
OFFlCER: You guys should've started earlier.

1435
01:45:31,290 --> 01:45:33,520
The prisoners have already exchanged gifts.

1436
01:45:33,559 --> 01:45:35,527
MARV: We missed the presents?

1437
01:45:35,561 --> 01:45:36,926
He made us hide out in a store...

1438
01:45:36,962 --> 01:45:39,590
so we could steal the charity money.

1439
01:45:39,632 --> 01:45:41,429
-Shut up, Marv! -Aah!

1440
01:45:42,435 --> 01:45:44,801
HARRY: You got the right to remain silent, you know.

1441
01:45:45,705 --> 01:45:46,933
He's a little cranky.

1442
01:45:47,006 --> 01:45:48,701
We just broke out of prison a few days ago.

1443
01:45:48,774 --> 01:45:51,436
Shut up, Marv! Jeez!

1444
01:45:51,510 --> 01:45:53,774
-Get them out of here. -Let's go.

1445
01:45:53,813 --> 01:45:55,508
MARV: Remember, if this makes the papers...

1446
01:45:55,548 --> 01:45:57,106
we're no longer the Wet Bandits.

1447
01:45:57,149 --> 01:45:58,776
We're the Sticky Bandits!

1448
01:45:58,818 --> 01:46:01,412
Ow! That's Sticky! That's "S"...

1449
01:46:01,454 --> 01:46:02,580
HARRY: Shut it!

1450
01:46:02,621 --> 01:46:03,952
MARV: "T," uh...

1451
01:46:03,989 --> 01:46:06,116
-"l." -"l."

1452
01:46:18,003 --> 01:46:19,493
OFFlCER: Mr. Duncan, it's all over.

1453
01:46:19,538 --> 01:46:21,699
We apprehended the thieves, and we recovered your money.

1454
01:46:21,774 --> 01:46:23,036
DUNCAN: Good. I want to get that money...

1455
01:46:23,109 --> 01:46:25,509
over to the Children's Hospital.

1456
01:46:25,544 --> 01:46:27,034
OFFlCER: I'll handle it personally.

1457
01:46:27,113 --> 01:46:28,580
DUNCAN: Thank you very much.

1458
01:46:28,614 --> 01:46:30,377
INSPECTOR: Excuse me, Mr. Duncan.

1459
01:46:30,416 --> 01:46:31,849
I found this note.

1460
01:46:31,884 --> 01:46:33,818
Looks like a kid broke your window.

1461
01:46:50,736 --> 01:46:53,398
Turtledoves.

1462
01:46:53,472 --> 01:46:54,632
Ohh.

1463
01:47:02,081 --> 01:47:03,776
KATE: Oh, excuse me. I'm looking for my son.

1464
01:47:03,816 --> 01:47:05,113
He's this boy right here.

1465
01:47:07,586 --> 01:47:08,848
Excuse me. Please help me.

1466
01:47:08,921 --> 01:47:10,047
This boy right here, have you seen him?

1467
01:47:10,122 --> 01:47:11,919
This one. Please?

1468
01:47:20,533 --> 01:47:22,000
I'm looking for my son.

1469
01:47:22,034 --> 01:47:24,002
He's been missing for two days.

1470
01:47:24,036 --> 01:47:25,503
OFFlCER: Have you filed a report?

1471
01:47:25,538 --> 01:47:27,005
KATE: Yes, of course we have.

1472
01:47:29,108 --> 01:47:30,473
Then trust us.

1473
01:47:30,509 --> 01:47:31,669
We'll handle it.

1474
01:47:33,579 --> 01:47:34,739
Oh.

1475
01:47:37,049 --> 01:47:38,209
But I'm his mother.

1476
01:47:39,919 --> 01:47:41,011
I realize that, ma'am...

1477
01:47:41,086 --> 01:47:42,576
but you're looking for a needle in a haystack.

1478
01:47:43,756 --> 01:47:45,246
Do you have kids?

1479
01:47:46,325 --> 01:47:47,451
Yes, ma'am.

1480
01:47:47,493 --> 01:47:49,461
And what would you do if one of them was missing?

1481
01:47:51,464 --> 01:47:54,558
I'd probably be doing the same thing you're doing.

1482
01:47:55,568 --> 01:47:56,728
Thank you.

1483
01:47:59,338 --> 01:48:01,465
Look, put yourself in your kid's shoes.

1484
01:48:01,507 --> 01:48:03,873
Where would you go? What would you do?

1485
01:48:03,909 --> 01:48:07,003
Me? I'd probably be lying dead in a gutter somewhere.

1486
01:48:08,514 --> 01:48:09,947
Oh, but not Kevin.

1487
01:48:09,982 --> 01:48:13,748
No. Kevin is so much stronger and braver than I am.

1488
01:48:15,154 --> 01:48:17,486
I know Kevin's fine. I'm sure he is.

1489
01:48:17,523 --> 01:48:19,320
Fine.

1490
01:48:19,358 --> 01:48:21,519
But he's still all by himself in a big city...

1491
01:48:22,895 --> 01:48:24,726
and he doesn't deserve that.

1492
01:48:24,763 --> 01:48:27,391
He deserves to be at home with his own family...

1493
01:48:27,433 --> 01:48:29,094
around his Christmas tree.

1494
01:48:32,771 --> 01:48:34,102
Oh, dear God.

1495
01:48:35,374 --> 01:48:36,602
I know where he is.

1496
01:48:37,576 --> 01:48:39,100
I need to get to Rockefeller Center.

1497
01:48:40,045 --> 01:48:41,171
Hop in.

1498
01:48:41,213 --> 01:48:42,737
Thank you.

1499
01:48:46,986 --> 01:48:49,045
KEVlN: I know I don't deserve a Christmas...

1500
01:48:49,121 --> 01:48:51,089
even if I did do a good deed.

1501
01:48:52,124 --> 01:48:53,682
I don't want any presents.

1502
01:48:53,759 --> 01:48:55,488
Instead, I want to take back...

1503
01:48:55,528 --> 01:48:58,190
every mean thing I ever said to my family....

1504
01:48:58,230 --> 01:49:00,460
even if they don't take back the things they said.

1505
01:49:00,499 --> 01:49:02,899
I don't care. I'll love all of them...

1506
01:49:03,903 --> 01:49:05,530
including Buzz.

1507
01:49:05,571 --> 01:49:09,337
If I can only see one, can I see my mother?

1508
01:49:09,375 --> 01:49:12,902
I'll never want another thing as long as I live.

1509
01:49:12,945 --> 01:49:14,412
I just want my mother.

1510
01:49:14,446 --> 01:49:16,346
I know I won't see her tonight...

1511
01:49:16,382 --> 01:49:18,907
but promise me I can see her again...

1512
01:49:18,951 --> 01:49:20,942
sometime, anytime.

1513
01:49:20,986 --> 01:49:24,922
Even if it's just once and only for a couple of minutes.

1514
01:49:24,990 --> 01:49:27,288
I just need to tell her I'm sorry.

1515
01:49:35,367 --> 01:49:36,527
Kevin?

1516
01:49:43,342 --> 01:49:44,502
Mom?

1517
01:49:47,212 --> 01:49:48,907
Wow. That worked fast.

1518
01:49:59,558 --> 01:50:00,855
KATE: Oh, Kevin.

1519
01:50:02,728 --> 01:50:04,628
Mom, I'm sorry.

1520
01:50:06,165 --> 01:50:07,655
I'm sorry, too.

1521
01:50:20,546 --> 01:50:22,207
KEVlN: Merry Christmas, Mom.

1522
01:50:24,550 --> 01:50:26,677
KATE: Merry Christmas, sweetheart.

1523
01:50:27,720 --> 01:50:29,085
Thank you.

1524
01:50:30,155 --> 01:50:31,383
Let's go.

1525
01:50:32,391 --> 01:50:33,858
KEVlN: How'd you know I was here?

1526
01:50:33,926 --> 01:50:35,154
KATE: I know you and Christmas trees...

1527
01:50:35,194 --> 01:50:36,786
and this is the biggest around.

1528
01:50:36,829 --> 01:50:38,023
KEVlN: Where's everybody else?

1529
01:50:38,063 --> 01:50:39,189
KATE: They're at the hotel.

1530
01:50:39,231 --> 01:50:40,892
They didn't like the palm trees, either.

1531
01:51:03,455 --> 01:51:04,888
[Snoring]

1532
01:51:25,044 --> 01:51:27,774
Holy smokes! It's morning!

1533
01:51:29,148 --> 01:51:30,945
It's Christmas morning, man.

1534
01:51:32,384 --> 01:51:34,682
Fuller, don't get your hopes up.

1535
01:51:34,753 --> 01:51:36,243
FULLER: Huh?

1536
01:51:36,321 --> 01:51:38,255
I don't think Santa Claus visits hotels.

1537
01:51:38,290 --> 01:51:40,758
Are you nuts? He's omnipresent.

1538
01:51:40,826 --> 01:51:42,521
He goes everywhere.

1539
01:51:44,163 --> 01:51:46,063
Hey, guys, wake up! It's Christmas!

1540
01:51:50,736 --> 01:51:51,862
Mom, Dad, it's Christmas!

1541
01:51:51,904 --> 01:51:53,064
FRANK: What?!

1542
01:51:56,675 --> 01:51:57,937
GlRL: What on earth?

1543
01:51:57,976 --> 01:51:59,466
JEFF: Come on. I wanna find out.

1544
01:52:04,983 --> 01:52:06,644
ROD: Oh, wow.

1545
01:52:06,719 --> 01:52:08,687
JEFF: Where did it all come from?

1546
01:52:08,721 --> 01:52:10,780
KEVlN: Mom! Dad! You got to see this!

1547
01:52:15,394 --> 01:52:17,294
-Gosh. -Peter!

1548
01:52:17,329 --> 01:52:18,694
BUZZ: Are you sure we're in the right room?

1549
01:52:20,032 --> 01:52:22,227
-Look at all this stuff! -Yeah!

1550
01:52:22,267 --> 01:52:24,360
-Oh, wow! -Look!

1551
01:52:25,037 --> 01:52:26,698
FRANK: Don't open any of mine. I mean it.

1552
01:52:26,739 --> 01:52:28,206
Who's Mr. Duncan?

1553
01:52:28,240 --> 01:52:30,299
KATE: Duncan? I don't know.

1554
01:52:30,342 --> 01:52:31,639
All right. Everyone just calm down.

1555
01:52:31,677 --> 01:52:34,373
Calm down. Hey, hey!

1556
01:52:34,413 --> 01:52:36,438
All right. Now...

1557
01:52:36,482 --> 01:52:41,215
if Kevin hadn't screwed up in the first place again...

1558
01:52:41,286 --> 01:52:44,847
then we wouldn't be in this most perfect and huge hotel room...

1559
01:52:44,923 --> 01:52:46,857
with a truckload of all this free stuff...

1560
01:52:46,892 --> 01:52:48,519
so...

1561
01:52:48,560 --> 01:52:49,686
I think it only fair...

1562
01:52:49,728 --> 01:52:52,356
that Kevin get to open up the first present.

1563
01:52:52,998 --> 01:52:54,124
Then I'll go...

1564
01:52:54,166 --> 01:52:55,793
and the rest of you, and so on.

1565
01:53:00,272 --> 01:53:02,900
Merry Christmas, Kev.

1566
01:53:02,941 --> 01:53:04,704
Merry Christmas, Buzz.

1567
01:53:07,379 --> 01:53:08,505
PETER: Merry Christmas, Kevin.

1568
01:53:08,547 --> 01:53:10,242
FRANK: OK, Kevin!

1569
01:53:10,282 --> 01:53:12,512
All right! Merry Christmas!

1570
01:53:14,586 --> 01:53:16,611
Enough of this gooey sh--

1571
01:53:16,688 --> 01:53:18,349
show...of emotion.

1572
01:53:18,423 --> 01:53:19,515
Everyone, let's dig in!

1573
01:53:19,591 --> 01:53:22,754
-All right! -Everybody, wait.

1574
01:53:22,795 --> 01:53:24,353
LESLlE: Save the paper. We can use it next year.

1575
01:53:24,396 --> 01:53:26,455
Give me the bows.

1576
01:54:02,034 --> 01:54:03,661
Merry Christmas.

1577
01:54:06,138 --> 01:54:07,571
Kevin!

1578
01:54:07,639 --> 01:54:09,266
Merry Christmas!

1579
01:54:10,275 --> 01:54:11,435
I got something for you.

1580
01:54:19,818 --> 01:54:20,910
What's this?

1581
01:54:20,986 --> 01:54:22,453
It's a turtledove.

1582
01:54:22,487 --> 01:54:24,421
I have one, you have one.

1583
01:54:24,456 --> 01:54:26,356
As long as we each have a turtledove...

1584
01:54:26,391 --> 01:54:27,915
we'll be friends forever.

1585
01:54:31,964 --> 01:54:34,228
Oh, Kevin.

1586
01:54:37,236 --> 01:54:39,397
Thank you.

1587
01:54:40,639 --> 01:54:42,903
I won't forget you. Trust me.

1588
01:54:51,650 --> 01:54:52,810
WOMAN: Oh.

1589
01:55:11,169 --> 01:55:13,399
Mr. McCallister's room service bill, sir.

1590
01:55:15,507 --> 01:55:16,701
Merry Christmas, sir.

1591
01:55:18,076 --> 01:55:19,236
Uh, oh.

1592
01:55:23,282 --> 01:55:24,977
Nice family.

1593
01:55:25,017 --> 01:55:26,507
Really.

